genresAdvancedInfo.name: spanish psychedelic rock
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Spanish psychedelic rock draws from the psychedelic and experimental sounds of the late 1960s and early 1970s, combining them with the rhythms and melodies of Spanish folk music. The genre is known for its use of trippy effects, surreal lyrics, and improvisation.
